==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Immure
<hw>Im*mure"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Immured</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Immuring</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Pref. <ets>im-</ets> in +
<ets>mure</ets>: cf. F. <ets>emmurer</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
wall around; to surround with walls.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Sandys.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To inclose within walls, or as within walls; hence,
to shut up; to imprison; to incarcerate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Those tender babes⟦br⟧
Whom envy hath <qex>immured</qex> within your walls.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This huge convex of fire,⟦br⟧
Outrageous to devour, <qex>immures</qex> us round.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Immure</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Immure
<hw>Im*mure"</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A wall; an inclosure.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Immurement</ent>⟦br⟧
